text.section:
In addition to the other powers granted to the board under this chapter, the board may, in connection with any person whom the board, after a hearing adjudges unqualified or whom the board, after a hearing, finds to have performed one (1) or more of the acts described in KRS 312.150:
Revoke the license to practice;
Suspend the license to practice;
Publicly reprimand or censure the person;
Place the person on probation for a period and upon the terms and conditions that the board may establish;
Require payment of all costs of proceedings resulting from the disciplinary action; and
Limit the license to practice.
